import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Date'])]
    
    plt.plot(data['Date'], data['CO2'], label='CO2 Concentration', color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('CO2 Concentration')
    plt.title('What is the trend of CO2 concentration over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['CO2'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='CO2 Concentration')
    plt.axvline(data['CO2'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['CO2'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('CO2 Concentration')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of CO2 concentration?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Date'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Date'].dt.year
    yearly_avg = data.groupby('Year')['CO2'].mean().reset_index()

    plt.bar(yearly_avg['Year'], yearly_avg['CO2'])
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Average CO2 Concentration')
    plt.title('What is the average CO2 concentration per year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from statsmodels.tsa.seasonal import seasonal_decompose

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Date'])]
    
    data.set_index('Date', inplace=True)
    decomposition = seasonal_decompose(data['CO2'], model='additive', period=12)
    
    fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(10, 6), sharex=True)
    
    ax1.plot(data.index, data['CO2'], label='CO2 Concentration', color='blue')
    ax1.plot(decomposition.seasonal, label='Seasonal Decomposition', color='red')
    ax1.set_title('Seasonal Pattern of CO2 Concentration')
    ax1.set_ylabel('CO2 Concentration')
    ax1.legend(loc='upper left')
    
    ax2.plot(decomposition.seasonal, label='Seasonal Component', color='green')
    ax2.set_title('Seasonal Component')
    ax2.set_ylabel('CO2 Concentration')
    ax2.legend(loc='upper left')
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
